    <p>{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Event Loop`}</inlineCode>{` itself is truly single threaded. This is commonly seen as a bad thing, as the event loop can only run on one CPU core.`}</p>
    <p>{`However, some of the functions included in the standard library of Node are not single threaded - they run outside of the event loop.`}</p>
